NNOOTTEESS
     _r_._b_u_f_f_e_r measures distances from center of cell to center of
     cell using Euclidean distance measure for planimetric
     databases (like UTM) and using ellipsoidal geodesic distance
     measure for latitude/longitude databases.

     _r_._b_u_f_f_e_r calculates distance zones from all cells having
     non-zero category values in the _i_n_p_u_t map.  If the user
     wishes to calculate distances from only selected _i_n_p_u_t map
     layer category values, the user should run (for example)
     _r_._r_e_c_l_a_s_s prior to _r_._b_u_f_f_e_r, to reclass all categories from
     which distance zones are not desired to be calculated into
     category zero.

